"72:7:8" : {s: 72, a: 7, w: 8, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهُ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-lahu", lb: "আল্লাহ ",e: "Allah", b: "আল্লাহ", f: 733, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
"72:7:9" : {s: 72, a: 7, w: 9, r: "احد", t: "أَحَدًۭا", l: "أَحَد", lc: 74, tl: "aḥadan", lb: "এক ",e: "anyone", b: "কাউকে", f: 20, rm: "make/call it one, unity, anyone/anything."},
"72:8:1" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 1, r: "", t: "وَأَنَّا", l: "أَنّ", lc: 343, tl: "Waanna", lb: "যে, যেন",e: "And that we", b: "আমরা", f: 8, rm: ""},
"72:8:2" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 2, r: "لمس", t: "لَمَسْنَا", l: "لَمَسُ", lc: 4, tl: "lamasnā", lb: "স্পর্শ করা",e: "sought to touch", b: "আমরা অনুসন্ধান করতে চাইলাম", f: 1, rm: "To touch, feel with the hand, to stretch towards, seek, inquire after, have intercourse."},
"72:8:3" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 3, r: "سمو", t: "ٱلسَّمَآءَ", l: "سَمَآء", lc: 310, tl: "l-samāa", lb: "আকাশ, মহাকাশ, আমাদের উপরে সব কিছু ",e: "the heaven", b: "বৃষ্টি", f: 13, rm: ""},
"72:8:4" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 4, r: "وجد", t: "فَوَجَدْنَٰهَا", l: "وَجَدَ", lc: 106, tl: "fawajadnāhā", lb: "পাওয়া, দেখতে পাওয়া",e: "but we found it", b: "আমরা সেটি পেলাম", f: 1, rm: "to find what was lost, perceive, obtain, find any one or anything (such and such)."},
"72:8:5" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 5, r: "ملا", t: "مُلِئَتْ", l: "مُلِئَتْ", lc: 6, tl: "muli-at", lb: "ভরা হয়েছে",e: "filled (with)", b: "পরিপূর্ণ হয়ে আছে", f: 1, rm: "To fill, satisfy, help. The sap or vigour of youth, or young manhood became fuller mantled in a person. Satisfy/Glut. Aid, assist, conform with to do a thing. Assembly. Utmost [such as pulling a bow as far back as possible]. The utmost of his power and ability was accomplished. Sufficient in quantity or dimension for filling. Disposition, nature [as one rich in needul qualities], manners. Principle persons, chiefs [because they are rich in needful things]. That which is satisfactory or satisfies [such as a majestic person]. An ewe in whose belly are water and matter so that one thinks her to be pregnant."},
"72:8:6" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 6, r: "حرس", t: "حَرَسًۭا", l: "حَرَس", lc: 1, tl: "ḥarasan", lb: "পাহাড়াদার",e: "guards", b: "প্রহরা, পাহারাদার", f: 1, rm: "To guard/keep/preserve, take care of a person or thing, watch over."},
"72:8:7" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 7, r: "شدد", t: "شَدِيدًۭا", l: "شَدِيد", lc: 56, tl: "shadīdan", lb: "কড়া",e: "severe", b: "কঠিন", f: 11, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard."},
"72:8:8" : {s: 72, a: 8, w: 8, r: "شهب", t: "وَشُهُبًۭا", l: "شُهُب", lc: 1, tl: "washuhuban", lb: "",e: "and flaming fires", b: "উল্কাপিণ্ড", f: 1, rm: "to burn/scorch, become of a colour in which whiteness predominates over blackness. shihaab (pl. shuhub) - flaming fire, bright blaze/meteor, star, penetrating flame, shining star, brisk/sprightly, flame, brand, radiating or gleaming fire, shooting or falling star. shihaab al-herb - dauntless warrior, one who is penetrating sharp and energetic in war."},
"72:9:1" : {s: 72, a: 9, w: 1, r: "", t: "وَأَنَّا", l: "أَنّ", lc: 343, tl: "Waanna", lb: "যে, যেন",e: "And that we", b: "আমরা", f: 8, rm: ""},
"72:9:2" : {s: 72, a: 9, w: 2, r: "كون", t: "كُنَّا", l: "كَانَ", lc: 1358, tl: "kunnā", lb: "হয়, হতো",e: "used to", b: "আমরা ছিলাম", f: 63, rm: "To be, exist, happen, occur, take place, become, be such or so, originated."},
"72:9:3" : {s: 72, a: 9, w: 3, r: "قعد", t: "نَقْعُدُ", l: "قَعَدَ", lc: 12, tl: "naqʿudu", lb: "বসা",e: "sit", b: "আমরা বসতাম", f: 1, rm: "to sit down, remain behind, to hold back, to tarry, lie in wait, sit still, remain unmoved, desist, abstain, refrain, lurk in ambush, set snares, neglect, act of sitting, foundations/bases, women who are past child bearing age, elderly spinsters past child bearing age, one who sits at home, one who sits still, seat or place of sitting, station, encampment."},
"72:9:4" : {s: 72, a: 9, w: 4, r: "", t: "مِنْهَا", l: "مِن", lc: 3067, tl: "minha", lb: "মধ্য থেকে, কিছুর চেয়ে",e: "there in", b: "তা হতে", f: 65, rm: ""},
"72:9:5" : {s: 72, a: 9, w: 5, r: "قعد", t: "مَقَٰعِدَ", l: "مَقْعَد", lc: 4, tl: "maqāʿida", lb: "আসন,",e: "positions", b: "ঘাটিঁসমূহে", f: 2, rm: "to sit down, remain behind, to hold back, to tarry, lie in wait, sit still, remain unmoved, desist, abstain, refrain, lurk in ambush, set snares, neglect, act of sitting, foundations/bases, women who are past child bearing age, elderly spinsters past child bearing age, one who sits at home, one who sits still, seat or place of sitting, station, encampment."},
